This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of deep learning models, specifically deep residual networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization and generalization guarantees, which suggests that it could also be categorized as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of deep residual networks on image classification tasks, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category. The paper also discusses the theoretical understanding of the improvement in performance of residual networks, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper discusses the architecture of deep neural networks, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category.
